Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Finely chop @sun-dried tomatoes{1.5%ounce}(finely chopped). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} lengthwise; place in a #small bowl{} and toss with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Pick @fresh parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1/3 cup pasta cooking water (1/2 cup for 4 servings), then drain.

While pasta cooks, heat a #large dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and cook, stirring often, until fragrant and lightly browned, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a second small bowl. Wipe out pan.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water. Pat shrimp dry with #paper towels{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for almonds over medium-high heat. Add shrimp; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for almonds over medium heat. Add sundried tomatoes and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1} and 1/3 cup plain water (1/2 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and whisk in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} until fully incorporated.

Stir grape tomatoes into pan with sauce. Add drained spaghetti, half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, and @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings); toss to combine.

> If needed, stir in reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Stir in half the chopped parsley. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat.

Stir shrimp into sauce along with spaghetti.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}. Top with toasted almonds, remaining Parmesan, and remaining chopped parsley. Serve.